text: St. George is an unincorporated community in West Newton Township, Nicollet County, Minnesota, United States, near New Ulm. The community is located near the junction of Nicollet County Roads 5 and 16. A post office called Saint George was established in 1894, and remained in operation until 1904. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Nicollet County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: St. George, Minnesota
